BoundAttributes.Name: AutoClose
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If true, the parent <see cref="T:Blazorise.Alert" /> or <see cref="T:Blazorise.Modal" /> with be automatically closed
            when <see cref="T:Blazorise.CloseButton" /> button is placed inside of them.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:

            </summary>

            eg: for the TextEdit the ID will be set on the input element.
            </remarks>

TagHelpers.Name: Blazorise.TextEdit
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            Component that allows you to display and edit single-line text.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Role
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines the role of the input text.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: InputMode
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Hints at the type of data that might be entered by the user while editing the element or its contents.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Text
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the text inside the input field.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: TextChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Occurs after text has changed.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: TextExpression
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets an expression that identifies the text value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EditMask
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A string representing a edit mask expression.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: MaskType
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specify the mask type used by the editor.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: MaxLength
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the maximum number of characters allowed in the input element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: VisibleCharacters
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The size attribute specifies the visible width, in characters, of an input element. https://www.w3schools.com/tags/att_input_size.asp".
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Placeholder
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Sets the placeholder for the empty text.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Plaintext
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Sets the class to remove the default form field styling and preserve the correct margin and padding.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Color
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Sets the input text color.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Pattern
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The pattern attribute specifies a regular expression that the input element's value is checked against on form validation.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ChangeTextOnKeyPress
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If true the text in will be changed after each key press.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            Note that setting this will override global settings in <see cref="P:Blazorise.BlazoriseOptions.ChangeTextOnKeyPress" />.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: DelayTextOnKeyPress
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If true the entered text will be slightly delayed before submiting it to the internal value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: DelayTextOnKeyPressInterval
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Interval in milliseconds that entered text will be delayed from submiting to the internal value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Size
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Sets the size of the input control.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ReadOnly
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Add the readonly boolean attribute on an input to prevent modification of the inputs value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Disabled
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Add the disabled boolean attribute on an input to prevent user interactions and make it appear lighter.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Autofocus
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Set's the focus to the component after the rendering is done.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Feedback
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Placeholder for validation messages.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ChildContent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Input content.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: KeyDown
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Occurs when a key is pressed down while the control has focus.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: KeyPress
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Occurs when a key is pressed while the control has focus.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: KeyUp
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Occurs when a key is released while the control has focus.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Blur
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The blur event fires when an element has lost focus.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnFocus
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Occurs when the input box gains or loses focus.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: FocusIn
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Occurs when the input box gains focus.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: FocusOut
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Occurs when the input box loses focus.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: TabIndex
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If defined, indicates that its element can be focused and can participates in sequential keyboard navigation.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CustomValidationValue
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Used to provide custom validation value on which the validation will be processed with
            the <see cref="P:Blazorise.Validation.Validator" /> handler.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            Should be used carefully as it's only meant for some special cases when input is used
            in a wrapper component, like Autocomplete or SelectList.
            </remarks>

            </summary>
            <remarks>

            eg: for the TextEdit the ID will be set on the input element.
            </remarks>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Mode
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines the validation mode for validations inside of this container.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ValidateOnLoad
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, and <see cref="P:Blazorise.Validations.Mode" /> is set to <see cref="F:Blazorise.ValidationMode.Auto" />, validation will run automatically on page load.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            When validation is placed inside of modal dialog, the behavior is a little different. 
            Modals are by definition always loaded and are always present in the DOM so no loading is ever happening again
            after the page that contains the modal is first initialized.  Their visibility is controlled by display: none;
            To workaround this, the actual "first load" for modals can be done by re-initializing <see cref="P:Blazorise.Validations.Model" /> parameter. 
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: EditContext
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Supplies the edit context explicitly. If using this parameter, do not
            also supply <see cref="P:Blazorise.Validations.Model" />, since the model value will be taken
            from the <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Forms.EditContext.Model" /> property.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Model
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the top-level model object for the form. An edit context will be constructed for this model.
            If using this parameter, do not also supply a value for <see cref="P:Blazorise.Validations.EditContext" />.
            </summary>

TagHelpers.Name: Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Authorization.AuthorizeRouteView
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
             Combines the behaviors of <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Authorization.AuthorizeView" /> and <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.RouteView" />,
             so that it displays the page matching the specified route but only if the user
             is authorized to see it.
            
             Additionally, this component supplies a cascading parameter of type <see cref="T:System.Threading.Tasks.Task`1" />,
             which makes the user's current authentication state available to descendants.
             </summary>

TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers.ITagHelper" /> implementation targeting elements containing attributes with URL expected values.
            </summary>
            <remarks>Resolves URLs starting with '~/' (relative to the application's 'webroot' setting) that are not
            targeted by other <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers.ITagHelper" />s. Runs prior to other <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers.ITagHelper" />s to ensure
            application-relative URLs are resolved.</remarks>

            <remarks>

            <see cref="M:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.ViewFeatures.IHtmlGenerator.GenerateTextBox(Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Rendering.ViewContext,Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.ViewFeatures.ModelExplorer,System.String,System.Object,System.String,System.Object)" />.

            helper to call and the default <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.InputTagHelper.Format" /> value. A default <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.InputTagHelper.Format" /> is not calculated
            if the provided (see <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.InputTagHelper.InputTypeName" />) or calculated "type" attribute value is <c>checkbox</c>,

TagHelpers.Name: Bind
TagHelpers.Documentation: Binds the provided expression to an attribute and a change event, based on the naming of the bind attribute. For example: @bind-value="..." and @bind-value:event="onchange" will assign the current value of the expression to the 'value' attribute, and assign a delegate that attempts to set the value to the 'onchange' attribute.

BoundAttributes.Name: @bind-...
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Binds the provided expression to an attribute and a change event, based on the naming of the bind attribute. For example: @bind-value="..." and @bind-value:event="onchange" will assign the current value of the expression to the 'value' attribute, and assign a delegate that attempts to set the value to the 'onchange' attribute.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: format
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies a format to convert the value specified by the corresponding bind attribute. For example: @bind-value:format="..." will apply a format string to the value specified in @bind-value="...". The format string can currently only be used with expressions of type DateTime.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: event
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies the event handler name to attach for change notifications for the value provided by the '@bind-...' attribute.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: culture
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies the culture to use for conversions.
